            <Header>Food 4 Thought</Header>
            <Slogan>Turning Trash Into Treasure.</Slogan>
        </r1c1>
        <r1c2>
        </r1c2>
        <r1c3>
            <!-- Button to open the modal login form -->
            <p></p><a onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='block'">Login</a></p>

            <!-- The Modal -->
            <div id="id01" class="modal">
            <span onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='none'"
                  class="close" title="Close Modal">&times;</span>

                <!-- Modal Content -->
                <form class="modal-content animate" action="/login" method="POST">
                    <div class="container">
                        <label for="username"><b>Username</b></label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Enter Username" name="username" required>

                        <label for="password"><b>Password</b></label>
                        <input type="password" placeholder="Enter Password" name="password" required>

                        <button type="submit">Login</button>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </r1c3>
        <r1c4>
            <!-- Button to open the modal login form -->
            <p><a onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='block'">Sign Up</a></p>

            <!-- The Modal -->
            <div id="id02" class="modal">
            <span onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='none'"
                  class="close" title="Close Modal">&times;</span>

                <!-- Modal Content -->
                <form action="/register" class="modal-content animate" method="POST">
                    <div class="imgcontainer">
                        <img src="assets/default_avatar.png" alt="Avatar" class="avatar">
                    </div>
                    <div class="container">
                        <label for="email"><b>Email Address</b></label>
                        <input type="email" placeholder="Enter an Email Address" name="email" required>
                        <label for="name"><b>Company Name</b></label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your Business' Name" name="name" required>
                        <label for="name"><b>Location</b></label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your Business' Name" name="address" required>
                        <label for="username"><b>Username</b></label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Enter a Username" name="username" required>
                        <label for="password"><b>Password</b></label>
                        <input type="password" placeholder="Enter Password" name="password" required>
                        <label for="phone"><b>Phone Number</b></label>
                        <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your Phone Number" name = "phone" required>
                        <label>
                            <input type="checkbox" name="type" value="charity"> Charity
                        </label>
                        <label>
                            <input type="checkbox" name="type" value="waster"> Waste Provider
                        </label>
                        <button type="submit">Sign Up!</button>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </r1c4>
        <r1c5>
            <p><a href="/" style="text-decoration: none">Home</a></p>
        </r1c5>
    </div>

    <div class="middle">
        <p>Food 4 Thought was created by a young group of guys who got sick and tired of throwing perfectly good food out.
        We worked in supermarkets, in restaurants and in cafes, never quite knowing why there was no one trying to pick
        all this stuff up. We understand that businesses have standards to maintain and that customers expect the best,
            so sometimes, good food gets thrown away. This is a reality of the industry.</p>
            <p>Food 4 Thought wants to empower businesses
        and charities. We're simply your platform. We want to make it easier for you to do the right thing.</p>
    </div>
</div>
